### Named Constructors

Dart classes can have multiple constructors with different names. This provides flexibility in object creation.

```dart
class Point {
  double x, y;

  // Primary constructor
  Point(this.x, this.y);

  // Named constructor
  Point.origin()
      : x = 0,
        y = 0;

  // Another named constructor
  Point.fromList(List<double> coords)
      : x = coords[0],
        y = coords[1];
}

void main() {
  var p1 = Point(3, 4);
  var p2 = Point.origin();
  var p3 = Point.fromList([5, 6]);
}
```

### Named Constructors with Initializer Lists

```dart
class Person {
  final String firstName;
  final String lastName;
  final int age;

  Person(this.firstName, this.lastName, this.age);

  // Named constructor with initializer list
  Person.fromFullName(String fullName, this.age)
      : firstName = fullName.split(' ')[0],
        lastName = fullName.split(' ').length > 1
            ? fullName.split(' ')[1]
            : '';

  // Named constructor with defaults
  Person.anonymous(this.age)
      : firstName = 'Unknown',
        lastName = 'Unknown';

  String get fullName => '$firstName $lastName';
}
```

### Redirecting Constructors

A constructor can delegate to another constructor in the same class.

```dart
class Point {
  double x, y;

  Point(this.x, this.y);

  // Redirects to the main constructor
  Point.origin() : this(0, 0);

  Point.fromXY(dynamic xVal, dynamic yVal) : this(xVal.toDouble(), yVal.toDouble());
}
```

### Named Constructors and Inheritance

Named constructors are NOT inherited by subclasses. Subclasses must define their own.

```dart
class Animal {
  String name;
  Animal(this.name);
  Animal.named(this.name);
}

class Dog extends Animal {
  Dog(String name) : super(name);

  // Must define own named constructor
  Dog.named(String name) : super.named(name);
}
```

> **Key Point:** Named constructors improve code readability by making the intent clear. Use them for common creation patterns like `Point.origin()`, `Color.fromRGB()`, or `DateTime.now()`.

codeExample:
class Temperature {
  double celsius;

  Temperature(this.celsius);

  // Named constructors
  Temperature.fromFahrenheit(double fahrenheit)
      : celsius = (fahrenheit - 32) * 5 / 9;

  Temperature.fromKelvin(double kelvin)
      : celsius = kelvin - 273.15;

  Temperature.freezing() : this(0);
  Temperature.boiling() : this(100);

  double get fahrenheit => celsius * 9 / 5 + 32;
  double get kelvin => celsius + 273.15;
}

void main() {
  var t1 = Temperature.fromFahrenheit(98.6);
  var t2 = Temperature.fromKelvin(300);
  var t3 = Temperature.freezing();

  print('Body temp: ${t1.celsius.toStringAsFixed(1)}C');
  print('Room temp: ${t2.fahrenheit.toStringAsFixed(1)}F');
  print('Freezing: ${t3.celsius}C');
}
